rComments: I really liked him. His class was simple and he taught beginner Spanish really well. He answered every email I sent pretty quickly, on par with what you'd expect from a professor. He was very caring and professional and I genuinely enjoyed his class. Quizzes were super easy and fully based off the course's grammar book so STUDY THAT!!!

He really does not know how to teach a language. It is obvious that he speaks spanish very well but his explanations to everything lack structure and clarity. It's still an easy A class though even with an awful prof because it's an easy subject to teach yourself

I don't understand the bad ratings. He answered every email I sent within 24 hours, and explained concepts very well. He spoke slow, which was useful to me since I have never taken Spanish before. He always took time to answer everyone's questions during lectures, and never acted annoyed if someone asked a "basic" question. 100/10 recommend.
Didn't answer emails, TA was terrible.

Doesn't give feedback, is not really accessible outside class nor via email, has no clear correction/evaluation criteria, theoretical texts used are at least 20yo, likes the sound of own voice, not very skilled at online teaching and has an obsolete take on the teaching of languages. Classes are really boring. Being online might not have helped.

This prof is AWFUL at replying to emails which is the worst type of prof to have with online school. Not impressed with his teaching or the class this semester. This prof didnt make online school bearable at all.

Do practice questions. prof would never answer his emails. Course consists of 5 quizzes, an oral exam, a reading exam, and listening exam, and a final final exam. Do note the last four are all within a week of each other, during finals period so be careful about time. TA guadalupe was disrespectful to me on the first class

Our teacher switched half way through the year and he was the replacement. His lectures arent bad but he over explains very simple concepts. Also he wont respond to emails. Not impressed with communication skills
Great professor. Really wants you to do well. DGDs are mandatory if you want a good mark. Weekly quizzes with a speaking test, written test, listening test, and final.
Great prof, and a really interesting and fun course. He goes out of his way to make the course more interesting for you. 10/10 would take again. +1 for TA Adriana, she's excellent as well!

WOnderful prof! Super interesting and passionate about latin american literature, the content of this class is super interesting, and the class discussions are fun! It hardly feels like a class, it's more like a bookclub. Prof Abanto is very understanding of students' varying levels of Spanish proficiency. As long as you participate you'll do well!
Amazing prof. cares about students success. He's super helpful.

Easy course, lots of grammar exercises but they make the quizzes quite easy. Doesn't often respond to emails but always very helpful during office hours. The last month of class is tough, with a bunch of tests and assignments, as well as the final exam. Other than that, it's a pretty light course. Learned a lot of Spanish too!

Good Professor, I found he did a good job teaching the class. I would definitely take the class again but I found it was a lot of memorization. I loved my TA Adriana, I thought she was really nice and very good at her job.
His classes are taught in english, french and spanish. He makes sure that everyone understands and is always smiling.
Charismatic prof that makes you want to listen, very funny.

Excellent prof! Had him in ESP1991 and I am taking him again in ESP 1992. You can tell that he cares about his students and that he enjoys what he does. I learned a lot from his lectures and even though grammar is dry, I admire that he still tried to make it fun by adding music. He and his TA's have made my first year at UOttawa delightful.

This prof is charming, funny, and gives interesting, clear, and engaging lectures. He makes learning a new language fun, and not as hard as you might think (but there is a lot of homework and a quiz every LEC). Frequent use of the textbook.  Il parle très bien français, donc j'encourage les étudiants francophones à prendre le cours aussi.
Great prof,  I never missed classed because I enjoyed his lectures, 100% recommend, he doesn't believe in stressed students so is always understanding !

Excellent professor. Both of his Spanish language courses are excellent. He's super helpful and cares tremendously about his students. Do the exercises he assigns for every class, attend every class, pay close attention and you'll have no problem getting over 90. He has a special gift for teaching. Apply yourself a bit you'll be glad.

Strict professor but lectures very well. Unfortunately the Spanish department has a habit of making tests and midterms incredibly difficult and only tangentially related to the covered course material. However, Luis himself is an excellent professor, though a strict marker. Would recommend if you want a challenge.

He's actually a really good professor, but I think he was definitely dealing with a lot of personal stuff, and it definitely came through in his class. Make sure you actually attend all the classes, and do well on the quizzes. Study the grammar a lot. He's quite a tough grader.

J'ai trouvé ce cours facile puisque c'est semblable au francais! la seule raison pour laquelle j'allais en classe était pour les quiz, sinon, ce n'est pas nécessaire. Il y a beaucoup d'évaluation en même temps à la fin de la session. Beaucoup de vocabulaire et GRAMMAIRE à apparendre par coeur, mais c'est beaucoup de logique aussi. Cours optionnel.

Professor Luis is a gentleman. Very friendly and charismatic person, always smiling and sharing humour. The course itself is pretty easy as long as you do your homework and practice enough. Exams and assignments are fair and the TA's are good. Expect to laugh a lot and make friends in this class! I definitely recommend this course with prof. Luis!

I was in Anne-Sophie Chiabaut's section - what a great class, I loved it! Took it as an elective and it was definitely an easy way to get a very good mark. All the TAs are fantastic and so much fun, I highly recommend!

Very hard level and class. I find that he didnt explain the content very well and we didn't practice grammar, writing or speaking enough. A lot of verb tenses and grammar to learn. My worst spanish class to date.
Great prof!! He's so enthusiastic! He makes learning a new language 10x funner. Also explains in both french and english every time someone asks a question!
He is the best, enough said.

What an amazing professor!! This is the third time I've had him and he's really inspired and encouraged me in learning the Spanish language. He's the program head and it shows. Luis is super dedicated and genuinely wants to help you succeed. 10/10!

Awesome prof! Extremely helpful and makes learning a new language seem easy. He loves what he does and is always willing to spend extra time with you if you need extra clarifications. If you're interested in learning spanish, try your best to get him as a teacher! Loved this class.
He is a very good teacher! :)
Just plain ans simple awesome
not interesting
Excellent teacher! Always available for questions.. very fun class!
Great prof! Very enthusiastic and makes learning fun!
Amazing teacher!!! Very enthused about teaching the Spanish language. He genuinely cares about his students and the subject matter.  He is always available for help in his office.
So enthusiastic, so helpful, so nice. Just a great, great teacher. Really hope to be in his class again!!
Great teacher. He knows how to ease you into it. I wish he taught the upper level spanish classes.
LOVE HIM! I always try to make sure I'm in his section.. not only is he a great teacher and hilarious, but hes sooo hot!
Fun, helpful, engaging and authentic
Absolutely wonderful! Entusiastic, funny, clear, helpful, cute ^^, and best of all, he will answer your questions during exams! : D
Solid Prof, likes the students and likes to teach. He is very organized and clear.
I really liked this prof for educational and entertainment purposes. Knows his stuff, as he IS spanish, and is also very good with English and French as well, which is very convinient.
